HEADWORD: Sexagesima
<hw>Sex`a*ges"i*ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fem.
of <ets>sexagesimus</ets> sixtieth, fr. <ets>sexaginta</ets>
sixty.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>The second Sunday before Lent; --
so called as being about the sixtieth day before Easter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

